1
00:00:55,160 --> 00:00:56,680
Anan.

2
00:00:56,760 --> 00:00:57,720
What should we do,

3
00:00:57,720 --> 00:00:58,360
Anan?

4
00:00:58,560 --> 00:00:59,080
Anan.

5
00:00:59,200 --> 00:01:00,280
Anan.

6
00:01:01,480 --> 00:01:01,800
Anan.

7
00:01:01,800 --> 00:01:02,760
Over here.

8
00:01:05,720 --> 00:01:06,880
My mom is being really tough this time.

9
00:01:06,880 --> 00:01:08,240
She even locked the door.

10
00:01:08,240 --> 00:01:10,100
You guys have to get me out of here.

11
00:01:13,080 --> 00:01:14,560
The window is locked too.

12
00:01:14,960 --> 00:01:16,620
Why is it so serious this time?

13
00:01:22,960 --> 00:01:24,090
Where are you going?

14
00:01:26,160 --> 00:01:26,920
I...

15
00:01:30,240 --> 00:01:30,680
I...

16
00:01:30,680 --> 00:01:32,140
Playing the guitar again?

17
00:01:32,960 --> 00:01:34,490
I'm just going out for a bit.

18
00:01:34,600 --> 00:01:35,560
The kid wants to go out for a while.

19
00:01:35,560 --> 00:01:37,000
Just let him go.

20
00:01:37,000 --> 00:01:38,680
Don't think I don't know what you're doing.

21
00:01:38,680 --> 00:01:40,000
You're itching for a beating, aren't you?

22
00:01:40,000 --> 00:01:41,060
Give me the guitar.

23
00:01:41,200 --> 00:01:42,400
Hand over the guitar.

24
00:01:46,120 --> 00:01:47,200
I've had enough!

25
00:01:47,600 --> 00:01:49,130
What have you had enough of?

26
00:01:50,120 --> 00:01:52,000
Anan, you promised me yourself

27
00:01:52,080 --> 00:01:53,479
that you wouldn't do music anymore.

28
00:01:53,479 --> 00:01:55,610
Have you ever asked me what I want to do?

29
00:01:55,960 --> 00:01:57,200
I've loved music since I was little.

30
00:01:57,200 --> 00:01:58,530
Do you understand that?

31
00:01:58,640 --> 00:02:00,900
I don't even play in front of you anymore.

32
00:02:01,000 --> 00:02:02,800
What exactly do you want from me?

33
00:02:02,880 --> 00:02:05,120
You said you'd manage the homestay properly,

34
00:02:05,120 --> 00:02:06,800
but you're back to this nonsense again.

35
00:02:06,800 --> 00:02:08,330
Now you're even lying to me.

36
00:02:08,440 --> 00:02:09,639
Playing guitar and forming a band,

37
00:02:09,639 --> 00:02:10,919
how is that nonsense?

38
00:02:11,039 --> 00:02:12,080
What has music ever done to you?

39
00:02:12,080 --> 00:02:13,520
What on earth do you want me to do?

40
00:02:13,520 --> 00:02:14,520
Bring me the lock.

41
00:02:22,160 --> 00:02:22,840
No way.

42
00:02:23,680 --> 00:02:25,140
We can't just wait around.

43
00:02:25,680 --> 00:02:27,210
I'm going to steal Anan out.

44
00:02:27,480 --> 00:02:28,480
Stop right there.

45
00:02:28,880 --> 00:02:30,160
Do you think the fire isn't big enough?

46
00:02:30,160 --> 00:02:31,360
You want to add fuel to the flames, don't you?

47
00:02:31,360 --> 00:02:32,720
So what should we do?

48
00:02:35,960 --> 00:02:37,820
The competition is in three days.

49
00:02:38,040 --> 00:02:40,040
Brother Liuma isn't going on stage.

50
00:02:40,560 --> 00:02:42,000
Just the two of us?

51
00:02:47,720 --> 00:02:49,250
I'll figure something out.

52
00:02:52,880 --> 00:02:53,210
1987.

53
00:02:54,160 --> 00:02:54,760
Come on.

54
00:02:55,079 --> 00:02:56,079
Taste my cooking.

55
00:02:56,079 --> 00:02:57,079
Thank you, Uncle.

56
00:02:58,480 --> 00:03:00,960
I have to say, that brat Anan really is something.

57
00:03:00,960 --> 00:03:03,000
He never brings you guys home for dinner.

58
00:03:03,000 --> 00:03:05,930
All day long, he just knows how to run around outside.

59
00:03:08,440 --> 00:03:09,280
I quit.

60
00:03:14,640 --> 00:03:15,320
Uncle.

61
00:03:16,320 --> 00:03:18,360
Anan really loves music.

62
00:03:18,680 --> 00:03:19,280
Besides,

63
00:03:19,320 --> 00:03:21,320
making music isn't a dead end.

64
00:03:23,160 --> 00:03:25,120
This competition won't take long.

65
00:03:25,560 --> 00:03:26,480
Could you please

66
00:03:26,480 --> 00:03:27,810
give him another chance

67
00:03:27,920 --> 00:03:29,120
and let him try again?

68
00:03:31,920 --> 00:03:33,400
I'll be honest with you.

69
00:03:34,160 --> 00:03:35,840
There's a reason

70
00:03:36,200 --> 00:03:38,000
why I don't let Anan study music.

71
00:03:43,600 --> 00:03:45,260
Alright, that's it for today.

72
00:03:45,280 --> 00:03:45,880
Okay, Bro.

73
00:03:45,880 --> 00:03:46,920
After a few more gigs,

74
00:03:46,920 --> 00:03:48,000
we'll get a better sound system.

75
00:03:48,000 --> 00:03:48,840
We have to, Bro.

76
00:03:48,840 --> 00:03:49,700
You got it, Bro.

77
00:03:49,720 --> 00:03:50,520
Let's go.

78
00:03:50,640 --> 00:03:51,680
Let's go.

79
00:04:01,160 --> 00:04:01,880
I'm off.

80
00:04:09,160 --> 00:04:10,200
Your aunt

81
00:04:10,560 --> 00:04:11,600
took Anan

82
00:04:11,880 --> 00:04:13,080
back to Lincang.

83
00:04:13,680 --> 00:04:15,560
Then she met me.

84
00:04:16,279 --> 00:04:17,480
She didn't want Anan

85
00:04:17,720 --> 00:04:19,579
to be like his biological father.

86
00:04:24,280 --> 00:04:25,320
In our family,

87
00:04:25,680 --> 00:04:27,160
nothing is bigger than heaven and earth,

88
00:04:27,160 --> 00:04:29,080
except for his mom.

89
00:04:29,760 --> 00:04:30,640
This time,

90
00:04:30,880 --> 00:04:33,120
his mom is really angry.

91
00:04:35,000 --> 00:04:36,200
I understand, Uncle.

92
00:04:39,720 --> 00:04:40,560
Mom.

93
00:04:41,080 --> 00:04:42,960
Mom, I really love music.

94
00:04:44,080 --> 00:04:46,159
Mom, let me go to the competition.

95
00:04:47,120 --> 00:04:49,400
Mom, please let me out.

96
00:05:10,520 --> 00:05:11,960
Anan.

97
00:05:12,280 --> 00:05:12,920
You...

98
00:05:14,080 --> 00:05:14,480
Hurry up.

99
00:05:14,480 --> 00:05:15,410
Why are you here?

100
00:05:16,000 --> 00:05:16,600
Come here.

101
00:05:18,080 --> 00:05:19,960
It's inside out. Can't you be reliable?

102
00:05:19,960 --> 00:05:20,560
Hurry.

103
00:05:20,640 --> 00:05:21,480
Faster.

104
00:05:21,760 --> 00:05:22,890
Why are you here too?

105
00:05:23,520 --> 00:05:24,280
Cut the crap.

106
00:05:26,160 --> 00:05:27,680
Let's go.

107
00:05:27,800 --> 00:05:29,730
Why is the paint on my wall peeling?

108
00:05:37,040 --> 00:05:38,440
You have to compensate me for it.

109
00:05:38,440 --> 00:05:40,640
Damn. They're really having an affair.

110
00:05:41,640 --> 00:05:42,400
Slow down.

111
00:05:43,960 --> 00:05:44,600
I...

112
00:05:59,320 --> 00:06:01,450
You taught them to do this, didn't you?

113
00:06:02,880 --> 00:06:03,520
Honey.

114
00:06:03,880 --> 00:06:05,360
I wouldn't dare.

115
00:06:05,840 --> 00:06:07,200
Don't play dumb with me.

116
00:06:07,560 --> 00:06:08,600
You're right, Honey.

117
00:06:08,600 --> 00:06:10,120
I'll go get those little brats,

118
00:06:10,120 --> 00:06:10,840
bring them back,

119
00:06:10,840 --> 00:06:12,240
and teach them a lesson. God.

120
00:06:12,240 --> 00:06:13,320
That's enough.

121
00:06:14,720 --> 00:06:16,240
Who cares if they live or die?

122
00:06:16,240 --> 00:06:17,320
Hurry up and open the door.

123
00:06:17,320 --> 00:06:19,000
We have a business to run. We need to make money.

124
00:06:19,000 --> 00:06:19,600
Yes.

125
00:06:22,280 --> 00:06:23,280
You can't even feed yourself,

126
00:06:23,280 --> 00:06:25,210
yet you still play music every day.

127
00:06:28,720 --> 00:06:29,600
Wait a minute.

128
00:06:33,840 --> 00:06:34,970
That was so intense.

129
00:06:35,120 --> 00:06:36,180
I feel like my heart

130
00:06:36,360 --> 00:06:37,720
is going to jump out of my chest.

131
00:06:37,720 --> 00:06:38,850
Save that for later.

132
00:06:38,960 --> 00:06:39,600
Bro,

133
00:06:40,280 --> 00:06:41,610
why do you have the keys?

134
00:06:43,200 --> 00:06:44,530
I just ran out like this.

135
00:06:44,720 --> 00:06:46,250
How am I supposed to go home?

136
00:06:51,960 --> 00:06:52,880
But

137
00:06:53,120 --> 00:06:54,280
I know all about Anan's hard work

138
00:06:54,280 --> 00:06:55,760
in music

139
00:06:55,960 --> 00:06:57,120
over these years.

140
00:07:01,640 --> 00:07:02,640
Thank you, Uncle.

141
00:07:05,440 --> 00:07:06,120
Uncle,

142
00:07:06,600 --> 00:07:07,660
what about Auntie?

143
00:07:08,360 --> 00:07:09,440
Don't worry.

144
00:07:09,920 --> 00:07:13,040
Your auntie's bark is worse than her bite.

145
00:07:13,280 --> 00:07:16,080
You need the right method to coax her.

146
00:07:16,320 --> 00:07:18,200
I'm an expert at that.

147
00:07:19,480 --> 00:07:20,560
Come on. Eat up.

148
00:07:28,680 --> 00:07:30,680
Stop fooling around. Hurry inside.

149
00:07:44,960 --> 00:07:46,440
We're going to win.

150
00:07:46,800 --> 00:07:48,360
We'll be the champions.

151
00:07:48,640 --> 00:07:49,360
Right.

152
00:07:51,560 --> 00:07:52,490
Let's practice.

153
00:08:14,120 --> 00:08:14,880
Now,

154
00:08:15,560 --> 00:08:16,600
just sing.

155
00:08:47,960 --> 00:08:48,490
Mangshi,

156
00:08:48,840 --> 00:08:49,160
Radio Calisthenics Band,

157
00:08:49,160 --> 00:08:49,520
Wildfire Club,

158
00:08:49,520 --> 00:08:50,080
Urticaria Band,

159
00:08:50,080 --> 00:08:50,720
The Tenant's Dog,

160
00:08:50,720 --> 00:08:52,360
Lost Bicycle.
